    "The John Coolidge Objects Laboratory at the Harvard Museums is named in his memory.": [],
    "Nicholas Adams characterized Coolidge as an architectural historian striving for a cohesive analytic for architecture, one which would honestly evaluate what Coolidge considered the \"wearisome pageant of rivals\" with genuine architectural innovation.": [],
    "He avoided an architecture that was typological or regional in its method.": [],
    "He eschewed architectural biography in favor of a history that examined social and economic factors.": [],
